The first noticeable growth of the error and ensemble variance is around 250 hPa (i.e. near the altitudes of the extratropical jets) for zonal wind, and around the North Pole for surface pressure.
After about a month, the true error grows quite rapidly at the highest model levels, near the ``sponge'' layer (see Section \ref{sec:CAM}).
